The paper focuses on using reinforcement learning to train a quadruped robot to perform complex locomotion tasks. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also introduces a hierarchical framework for learning, which involves a high-level policy and a low-level policy. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also involves using on-board sensors to control the robot's actuators, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper tests the framework on a path-following task, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) to detect the path.
